HEADWORD: Audile
<hw>Au"dile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>audire</ets>
to hear.]</ety> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>One whose thoughts take the
form of mental sounds or of internal discourse rather than of visual or
motor images.</def>⟦br⟧
